listitem.para:
					Types generated by typegen can now be used in scripting
					in an intuitive way. For example
					  // old 2.0 style:
var /Bar bar = createBar();
var /std/vector</Bar> bars; // constructor does not work

// new 2.1 style:
var Bar bar2 = createBar();
// creates 10 Bar elements, each a copy of 'bar2':
var std.vector<Bar> bars2 = std.vector<Bar>(10, bar2 );

					Both the constructor and the type name accept the new
					'dotted' notation.
